{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EQSyjd1uBAh6yQU1sqBh97","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01P8MEsbpN4pXe6Rk2kuwXbR","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts","limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8098,"cache_read_input_tokens":50180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8098,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PEFENHuj6MhCVhrNkDt4mq","session_id":"0ef57e86-e719-4cc8-af9e-8c35c2cc8927","uuid":"6ae38d48-4bc2-406f-90d1-a16702efaeef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P8MEsbpN4pXe6Rk2kuwXbR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Settlement worker — polls the chain for PHASE_LOCKED CoinflipMatch accounts\n     3→ * co-signed by this server and detects when they are ready for settlement.\n     4→ */\n     5→\n     6→import { Connection, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     7→import bs58 from \"bs58\";\n     8→import { COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID } from \"../fairness.js\";\n     9→import type { Db } from \"../db.js\";\n    10→import { logger } from \"../logger.js\";\n    11→\n    12→// CoinflipMatch account layout offsets (includes 8-byte Anchor discriminator)\n    13→const ACCOUNT_SIZE = 246;\n    14→const SERVER_OFFSET = 72;\n    15→const PHASE_OFFSET = 114;\n    16→const TARGET_SLOT_OFFSET = 148;\n    17→\n    18→const PHASE_LOCKED_VALUE = 1;\n    19→\n    20→export interface SettlementWorkerDeps {\n    21→  db: Db;\n    22→  connection: Connection;\n    23→  serverKey: PublicKey;\n    24→  pollIntervalMs: number;\n    25→  /** Called when a match is detected as ready for settlement (target_slot reached). */\n    26→  onSettleReady?: (pda: string) => Promise<void>;\n    27→}\n    28→\n    29→export interface SettlementWorker {\n    30→  start(): void;\n    31→  stop(): void;\n    32→  readonly isRunning: boolean;\n    33→  /** Run a single poll cycle (exposed for testing). */\n    34→  poll(): Promise<void>;\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→export function createSettlementWorker(\n    38→  deps: SettlementWorkerDeps,\n    39→): SettlementWorker {\n    40→  const { db, connection, serverKey, pollIntervalMs } = deps;\n    41→  const discoveredPdas = new Set<string>();\n    42→  let running = false;\n    43→  let timeoutId: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | null = null;\n    44→\n    45→  async function poll(): Promise<void> {\n    46→    const currentSlot = await connection.getSlot();\n    47→\n    48→    // Query chain for PHASE_LOCKED CoinflipMatch accounts with our server key\n    49→    const accounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, {\n    50→      filters: [\n    51→        { dataSize: ACCOUNT_SIZE },\n    52→        {\n    53→          memcmp: {\n    54→            offset: PHASE_OFFSET,\n    55→            bytes: bs58.encode(Uint8Array.from([PHASE_LOCKED_VALUE])),\n    56→          },\n    57→        },\n    58→        {\n    59→          memcmp: {\n    60→            offset: SERVER_OFFSET,\n    61→            bytes: serverKey.toBase58(),\n    62→          },\n    63→        },\n    64→      ],\n    65→    });\n    66→\n    67→    for (const { pubkey, account } of accounts) {\n    68→      const pda = pubkey.toBase58();\n    69→      const data = Buffer.from(account.data);\n    70→\n    71→      // Parse target_slot (u64 LE at offset 148)\n    72→      const targetSlot = data.readBigUInt64LE(TARGET_SLOT_OFFSET);\n    73→\n    74→      // Log match_detected for newly discovered locked matches\n    75→      if (!discoveredPdas.has(pda)) {\n    76→        discoveredPdas.add(pda);\n    77→\n    78→        const round = await db.getRoundByPda(pda);\n    79→        if (round && round.phase === \"created\") {\n    80→          // Transition from created → locked in DB\n    81→          await db.updateRoundPhase(pda, \"locked\", {\n    82→            target_slot: targetSlot.toString(),\n    83→          });\n    84→          await db.insertOperatorEvent(pda, \"match_detected\", {\n    85→            targetSlot: targetSlot.toString(),\n    86→            currentSlot,\n    87→          });\n    88→        } else if (!round) {\n    89→          // Match on-chain but not in our DB — we don't have the secret, skip\n    90→          continue;\n    91→        }\n    92→      }\n    93→\n    94→      // Check if target_slot reached — match is ready for settlement\n    95→      if (BigInt(currentSlot) >= targetSlot && deps.onSettleReady) {\n    96→        await deps.onSettleReady(pda);\n    97→      }\n    98→    }\n    99→  }\n   100→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PEFENHuj6MhCVhrNkDt4mq","session_id":"0ef57e86-e719-4cc8-af9e-8c35c2cc8927","uuid":"09a87018-2d5e-4db1-94ee-20473059ec20"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a685e96978330c80b","tool_use_id":"toolu_01PEFENHuj6MhCVhrNkDt4mq","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore backend test and route code","usage":{"total_tokens":61371,"tool_uses":22,"duration_ms":72066},"uuid":"5c6bd49a-5e02-4596-89b1-84d2ab70b77c","session_id":"0ef57e86-e719-4cc8-af9e-8c35c2cc8927"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PEFENHuj6MhCVhrNkDt4mq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the backend codebase structure:\n\n## Complete Backend Codebase Overview\n\nI've read all the files you requested. Here's the comprehensive structure:\n\n### **Architecture & Entry Point**\n\n**`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`**\n- Hono web framework setup\n- Routes wired: `/fairness/coinflip`, `/fairness/rounds`, `/health`\n- Middleware stack: rate-limiting → auth (both on `/fairness/*`)\n- Settlement worker + retry settler launched on startup\n- Database and RPC connection initialized from config\n\n### **Configuration & Database**\n\n**`config.ts`**\n- `loadConfig()` reads env vars: PORT, DATABASE_URL, RPC_URL, SERVER_KEYPAIR, AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS, RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET, RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL, WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS, ENTROPY_ACCOUNT, MIN_SOL_BALANCE\n- Returns typed `Config` interface with defaults (port 3100, rate limits 10/100, clock skew 60s)\n- `parseKeypair()` expects JSON array of secret key bytes\n\n**`db.ts`** (Postgres client with typed queries)\n- `Round` type: pda, game, creator, server_key, secret, commitment, tier, side, nonce, phase, target_slot, settle_tx, settle_attempts, result_hash, result_side, winner, created_at, updated_at\n- `RoundPhase` enum: \"created\" → \"locked\" → \"settling\" → \"settled\" OR \"created\" → \"expired\" (unidirectional state machine)\n- `OperatorEvent` type: audit log with id, pda, event_type (secret_generated, tx_built, match_detected, settle_submitted, settle_confirmed, settle_failed, settle_retried, timeout_detected), payload, created_at\n- Methods: `insertRound()`, `updateRoundPhase()`, `getRoundByPda()`, `getRoundsByPhase()`, `insertOperatorEvent()`, `getUnsettledStats()`, `close()`\n- Phase transitions validated before DB write (e.g., can't go from settled → anything)\n\n**`logger.ts`**\n- JSON structured logging: timestamp, level (debug/info/warn/error), message, context fields\n- Errors to stderr, others to stdout\n\n### **Middleware**\n\n**`middleware/auth.ts`**\n- Ed25519 signature verification over canonical JSON: `{ wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp }`\n- Base58 encoding for signature and public key\n- Timestamp freshness check with configurable clock skew (default 60s)\n- GET requests bypass auth\n- Returns 401 on invalid/expired/missing fields\n- Signature must be 64 bytes, pubkey must be 32 bytes\n\n**`middleware/rate-limit.ts`**\n- In-memory sliding window (resets on restart, MVP acceptable)\n- Per-wallet limit (keyed by `wallet` field in body) + global limit\n- POST requests only; GET passes through\n- Returns 429 with `Retry-After` header when either limit hit\n- Timestamp-based cleanup (removes expired entries from window)\n\n### **Routes & Handlers**\n\n**`routes/create.ts`** — POST /fairness/coinflip/create\n- Request validation: wallet (valid base58 pubkey), tier (0-255), side (0 or 1), nonce (non-negative int), timestamp (unix seconds), signature (base58)\n- Generates 32-byte random secret + sha256 commitment\n- Derives match PDA from seeds: [\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]\n- Checks for duplicate PDA (409 Conflict if exists)\n- Builds partially-signed transaction (server signs, creator will sign client-side)\n- Inserts round into DB (phase: \"created\")\n- Logs operator event: \"secret_generated\"\n- Returns: `{ transaction (base64), matchPda, commitment (hex) }`\n\n**`routes/rounds.ts`** — GET /fairness/rounds/:pda\n- Fetches round from DB by PDA\n- Returns 404 if not found\n- Response format (camelCase): pda, game, phase, creator, commitment, tier, side, nonce, createdAt, updatedAt, targetSlot (if set)\n- **Only settled rounds expose**: secret (hex), resultHash (hex), resultSide, winner, settleTx\n- **Settled rounds include verification object**: commitmentCheck (sha256 formula), resultFormula, entropySource\n\n**`routes/health.ts`** — GET /health\n- DB connectivity check via `getUnsettledStats()`\n- Server SOL balance from RPC (lamports → SOL)\n- Warns if balance below threshold\n- Response: status, version, serverKey (base58), solBalance, dbConnected, workerRunning, unsettledCount, oldestUnsettledAge (seconds)\n\n### **Fairness Module**\n\n**`fairness.ts`**\n- `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`: \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"\n- `generateSecret()`: 32-byte cryptographic random\n- `computeCommitment(secret)`: sha256(secret) → Buffer\n- `deriveMatchPda(creator: PublicKey, nonce)`: PDA with seeds [\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()] (matches on-chain derivation)\n\n**`tx-builder.ts`**\n- `buildCreateMatchTx()`: constructs unsigned transaction for create_match instruction\n- Instruction data: discriminator (8) + commitment (32) + tier (1) + side (1) + nonce (8) = 50 bytes\n- Instruction keys: creator (signer, writable), server (signer, readonly), matchPda (writable), configPda (readonly), SystemProgram\n- Creator is fee payer; server partially signs; client must co-sign\n- Returns base64-serialized transaction + matchPda\n\n### **Worker**\n\n**`worker/settlement.ts`**\n- Polls chain for PHASE_LOCKED CoinflipMatch accounts co-signed by this server\n- Filters by account size (246 bytes), phase offset (114) = 1, server key match\n- Parses target_slot from offset 148 (u64 LE)\n- On discovery: transition DB from \"created\" → \"locked\", log \"match_detected\" event with targetSlot\n- When current slot >= target_slot: calls `onSettleReady(pda)` to trigger settlement\n- Exposed `poll()` method for testing\n\n### **Test Files (All Present)**\n\n**`fairness.test.ts`**\n- Tests `generateSecret()`: 32-byte uniqueness\n- Tests `computeCommitment()`: sha256 correctness, determinism, known vector\n- Tests `deriveMatchPda()`: PDA derivation, bump seed range, different creators/nonces\n\n**`auth.test.ts`**\n- Valid signature acceptance\n- Signature verification: invalid signature, wrong keypair, expired timestamp, missing fields\n- Accepts timestamps within clock skew\n- GET requests bypass auth\n- Tests canonical payload field ordering\n\n**`rate-limit.test.ts`**\n- Per-wallet limit enforcement\n- Global limit enforcement\n- Independent wallet tracking\n- Retry-After header presence and value\n- GET requests bypass rate limiting\n\n**`integration.test.ts`**\n- Full lifecycle: create → join (mock) → settle → verify\n- Mock Connection class: in-memory account storage, filters (dataSize, memcmp)\n- Builds match account data (246 bytes, specific offsets for creator, opponent, server, tier, entry, phase, commitment, target_slot, nonce)\n- Tests DB state transitions (created → locked → settling → settled)\n- Tests operator event trail\n- Tests settlement worker discovery + retry settler\n- Tests GET /rounds/:pda returns secret only when settled\n- Tests duplicate nonce returns 409\n- Tests unsettled round doesn't expose secret\n\n### **Package & Config**\n\n**`package.json`**\n- Name: @rng-utopia/backend\n- Scripts: dev (tsx watch), test (vitest), lint (eslint), typecheck (tsc), migrate (postgres)\n- Main deps: @solana/web3.js, hono, postgres, bs58, tweetnacl\n- Dev deps: @rng-utopia/config (workspace), typescript, tsx, vitest\n\n**`vitest.config.ts`**\n- Node environment, standard setup\n\n---\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Stateless endpoints** — request validation, DB write, response. No state stored in memory except rate-limit windows.\n2. **Canonical JSON signing** — exact key ordering in auth payload to prevent signature mismatches.\n3. **Phase state machine** — enforced unidirectional transitions; backend rejects invalid moves.\n4. **Secret confidentiality** — backend generates, stores in DB, only reveals after settlement.\n5. **Operator event audit trail** — every step logged: secret generation, detection, settlement attempts, confirmation.\n6. **Worker polling** — background process discovers locked matches, coordinates settlement via retry settler.\n7. **Mock-friendly** — Connection abstraction allows testing with in-memory accounts.\n\nAll files are present and ready for reading. The codebase is well-organized, testable, and follows TypeScript best practices."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a685e96978330c80b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63626\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 72077</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ef57e86-e719-4cc8-af9e-8c35c2cc8927","uuid":"468e2f73-ce76-4bb4-908f-8aba17730343","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the services/backend/ directory in /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/. I need to understand:\n\n1. The existing test files in src/__tests__/ - read ALL of them fully (fairness.test.ts, auth.test.ts, rate-limit.test.ts, integration.test.ts)\n2. The route handlers: src/routes/create.ts, src/routes/rounds.ts, src/routes/health.ts\n3. The main index.ts to see how routes are wired\n4. The middleware files: src/middleware/auth.ts, src/middleware/rate-limit.ts\n5. The config.ts, db.ts, and fairness.ts files\n6. package.json and vitest.config.ts\n\nRead ALL these files in full. I need to understand the complete codebase to write HTTP endpoint tests.","agentId":"a685e96978330c80b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the backend codebase structure:\n\n## Complete Backend Codebase Overview\n\nI've read all the files you requested. Here's the comprehensive structure:\n\n### **Architecture & Entry Point**\n\n**`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`**\n- Hono web framework setup\n- Routes wired: `/fairness/coinflip`, `/fairness/rounds`, `/health`\n- Middleware stack: rate-limiting → auth (both on `/fairness/*`)\n- Settlement worker + retry settler launched on startup\n- Database and RPC connection initialized from config\n\n### **Configuration & Database**\n\n**`config.ts`**\n- `loadConfig()` reads env vars: PORT, DATABASE_URL, RPC_URL, SERVER_KEYPAIR, AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS, RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET, RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL, WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS, ENTROPY_ACCOUNT, MIN_SOL_BALANCE\n- Returns typed `Config` interface with defaults (port 3100, rate limits 10/100, clock skew 60s)\n- `parseKeypair()` expects JSON array of secret key bytes\n\n**`db.ts`** (Postgres client with typed queries)\n- `Round` type: pda, game, creator, server_key, secret, commitment, tier, side, nonce, phase, target_slot, settle_tx, settle_attempts, result_hash, result_side, winner, created_at, updated_at\n- `RoundPhase` enum: \"created\" → \"locked\" → \"settling\" → \"settled\" OR \"created\" → \"expired\" (unidirectional state machine)\n- `OperatorEvent` type: audit log with id, pda, event_type (secret_generated, tx_built, match_detected, settle_submitted, settle_confirmed, settle_failed, settle_retried, timeout_detected), payload, created_at\n- Methods: `insertRound()`, `updateRoundPhase()`, `getRoundByPda()`, `getRoundsByPhase()`, `insertOperatorEvent()`, `getUnsettledStats()`, `close()`\n- Phase transitions validated before DB write (e.g., can't go from settled → anything)\n\n**`logger.ts`**\n- JSON structured logging: timestamp, level (debug/info/warn/error), message, context fields\n- Errors to stderr, others to stdout\n\n### **Middleware**\n\n**`middleware/auth.ts`**\n- Ed25519 signature verification over canonical JSON: `{ wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp }`\n- Base58 encoding for signature and public key\n- Timestamp freshness check with configurable clock skew (default 60s)\n- GET requests bypass auth\n- Returns 401 on invalid/expired/missing fields\n- Signature must be 64 bytes, pubkey must be 32 bytes\n\n**`middleware/rate-limit.ts`**\n- In-memory sliding window (resets on restart, MVP acceptable)\n- Per-wallet limit (keyed by `wallet` field in body) + global limit\n- POST requests only; GET passes through\n- Returns 429 with